Today it is 25 days that Pope Francis is admitted to the polyclinic Agostino Gemelli of Rome. After the weekend animated by the Jubilee of the volunteers this morning, also complicit in bad weather, there are few faithful who sit down to pray under the statue of St. John Paul II on the main square of the polyclinic. In the night in Rome a lot of rain fell and candles, votive lights and the many messages that the faithful put under the statue of the holy pope immediately with all evidence the consequences. There are few waxes still lit while barely you can read the messages on the drawings left by children. Few journalists present at the moment.&nbsp;

