The incidence of premature infants (born before 37 weeks of gestation) in Italy ranges between 7 and 10%, meaning about 25 thousand -30 thousand born a year. In the last decade, the combined obstetric-neonatological management has greatly changed the incidence of the preterminal parts and survival, especially of the lowest gestational age, but above all has improved the outcome of the preterminal infants, that is the remote outcome of neuromotor, cognitive and behavioral disabilities.
"To enter a neonatal intensive care department means to confront each day with the subtle border between fragility and trust in the future – concludes Quercia. Premature infants or severe pathologies are incredibly small beings, but with an extraordinary force.> For me, being here means having the privilege of accompanying them, together with their families, on a path that, thanks to the science and dedication of all staff, can lead to great victories." And so, in this corner of hope and struggle for life, music and medicine intertwine, creating a symphony that, like a heartbeat, reminds us that, even in the darkest moment, a vital spark can always resonate with sweetness and love.&nbsp;
